# gstack Skills

This repo includes [gstack](https://github.com/garrytan/gstack) — a workflow toolkit providing specialized AI agent skills. These are installed as a git submodule at `.claude/skills/gstack/`.

## Available Skills

| Skill | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `/ship` | Automated release: merge main, run tests, review diff, bump VERSION, update CHANGELOG, commit, push, create PR |
| `/review` | Pre-landing PR review analyzing diffs for SQL safety, trust boundary violations, side effects |
| `/plan-ceo-review` | Founder/CEO mode: rethink problems from first principles, find the 10-star product |
| `/plan-eng-review` | Engineering manager mode: lock in execution plans with architecture and edge cases |
| `/browse` | Fast headless browser (~100ms/cmd) for QA testing and site verification |
| `/qa` | Systematic QA testing with diff-aware, full, quick, and regression modes |
| `/retro` | Weekly engineering retrospective analyzing commit history and code quality |
| `/setup-browser-cookies` | Import authenticated browser sessions for testing |
| `/gstack-upgrade` | Upgrade gstack to latest version |

## When gstack conflicts with other commands

gstack commands are **canonical** — if a gstack skill conflicts with any other command or workflow, the gstack version takes precedence.

## Setup

gstack requires Bun (v1.0+). The session-start hook installs Bun and runs gstack setup automatically. For manual setup:

```bash
cd .claude/skills/gstack && ./setup
```
